{"TopicId":161621,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"[answered] How to change COM of a part in the cfg file","CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-05T11:05:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-05T11:05:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSubject says it all. \u00A0I have a number of parts for which I want to lower the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E a bit. \u00A0I can\u0027t find any documentation anywhere on how to do this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it possible, and if so, how?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: \u00A0Got the answer from a Twitch viewer:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\nCoMOffset = 0, 0, -0.5\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#272a34;\u0022\u003ENote sure what directions those are, but I\u0027m guessing X, Y and Z offset.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-05T11:38:35Z\u0022 title=\u002206/05/2017 11:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by linuxgurugamer\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Phineas Freak","CreatedById":146521,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T07:55:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223081013\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161621\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496660710\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m guessing X, Y and Z offset.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClose. KSP uses a different reference frame that uses a X, \u003Cstrong\u003EZ\u003C/strong\u003E and Y setup instead of the normal cartesian setup (this is valid for anything that accepts 3D coordinates, from \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E to MODEL position and scale). To save you from some frustration down the road...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}